<h1 id='groups'>Groups</h1><h2 id='create-a-group'>Create a Group</h2><pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code>curl <span class="s2">"https://community.tribe.so/api/v1/groups"</span>
  -H <span class="s2">"Authorization: Bearer {access_token}"</span>
  -X POST
</code></pre><pre class="highlight javascript tab-javascript"><code><span class="kr">const</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">require</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'tribe'</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="kd">let</span> <span class="nx">api</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">authorize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'{access_token}'</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="kd">let</span> <span class="nx">group</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">api</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">group</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">create</span><span class="p">({</span> <span class="p">...</span> <span class="p">});</span>
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p>The above command returns JSON structured like this:</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight json tab-json"><code></code></pre>
<p>This endpoint creates a new group. Only for admins.</p>
<h3 id='http-request'>HTTP Request</h3>
<p><code class="request">POST /api/v1/groups</code></p>
<h3 id='query-parameters'>Query Parameters</h3>
<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Parameter</th>
<th>Default</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>name</td>
<td></td>
<td>Name of the group to create</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>slug</td>
<td></td>
<td>Slug of the group to create</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>color</td>
<td></td>
<td>Color of the group to create</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>type</td>
<td><code>general</code></td>
<td>Type of the group to create. It can be one the followings: [<code>blog</code>, <code>general</code>, <code>feedback</code>]</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>description</td>
<td></td>
<td>Description of the group to create</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>privacy</td>
<td><code>public</code></td>
<td>Group privacy. It can be one of the followings: [<code>public</code>, <code>private</code>, <code>secret</code>]</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>verified</td>
<td></td>
<td>Is group verified?</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>picture</td>
<td></td>
<td>Picture URL of the group</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>banner</td>
<td></td>
<td>Banner URL of the group</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>registration</td>
<td><code>open</code></td>
<td>Registration of the group. It can be one of the followings: [<code>open</code>, <code>invitation</code>, <code>approval</code>, <code>none</code>]</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2 id='delete-a-group'>Delete a Group</h2><pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code>curl <span class="s2">"https://community.tribe.so/api/v1/groups/:id"</span>
  -H <span class="s2">"Authorization: Bearer {access_token}"</span>
  -X DELETE
</code></pre><pre class="highlight javascript tab-javascript"><code><span class="kr">const</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">require</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'tribe'</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="kd">let</span> <span class="nx">api</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">authorize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'{access_token}'</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="nx">api</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">group</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">remove</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">id</span><span class="p">);</span>
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p>The above command returns JSON structured like this:</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight json tab-json"><code><span class="p">{</span><span class="w"> 
  </span><span class="s2">"success"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="kc">true</span><span class="w"> 
</span><span class="p">}</span><span class="w">
</span></code></pre>
<p>This endpoint removes a specific group. Only for admins.</p>
<h3 id='http-request-2'>HTTP Request</h3>
<p><code class="request">DELETE /api/v1/groups/:id</code></p>
<h2 id='add-a-member'>Add a Member</h2><pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code>curl <span class="s2">"https://community.tribe.so/api/v1/groups/:id/members"</span>
  -H <span class="s2">"Authorization: Bearer {access_token}"</span>
  -X POST
  --DATA <span class="s2">"{}"</span>
</code></pre><pre class="highlight javascript tab-javascript"><code><span class="kr">const</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">require</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'tribe'</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="kd">let</span> <span class="nx">api</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">authorize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'{access_token}'</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="nx">api</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">group</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">addMember</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">id</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="nx">member</span><span class="p">);</span>
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p>The above command returns JSON structured like this:</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight json tab-json"><code></code></pre>
<p>This endpoint adds a user to a specific group. Only for admins.</p>
<h3 id='http-request-3'>HTTP Request</h3>
<p><code class="request">POST /api/v1/groups/:id/members</code></p>

<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Parameter</th>
<th>Default</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>user</td>
<td></td>
<td>ID of the user to add</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2 id='remove-a-member'>Remove a Member</h2><pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code>curl <span class="s2">"https://community.tribe.so/api/v1/groups/:id/members/:userId"</span>
  -H <span class="s2">"Authorization: Bearer {access_token}"</span>
  -X DELETE
</code></pre><pre class="highlight javascript tab-javascript"><code><span class="kr">const</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">require</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'tribe'</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="kd">let</span> <span class="nx">api</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">authorize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'{access_token}'</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="nx">api</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">group</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">removeMember</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">id</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="nx">member</span><span class="p">);</span>
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p>The above command returns JSON structured like this:</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight json tab-json"><code></code></pre>
<p>This endpoint removes a user from a specific group. Only for admins.</p>
<h3 id='http-request-4'>HTTP Request</h3>
