<h2 id='add-a-topic-to-group'>Add a Topic to Group</h2><pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code>curl <span class="s2">"https://community.tribe.so/api/v1/groups/:id/topics"</span>
  -H <span class="s2">"Authorization: Bearer {access_token}"</span>
  -X DELETE
  --DATA <span class="s2">"{...}"</span>
</code></pre><pre class="highlight javascript tab-javascript"><code><span class="kr">const</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">require</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'tribe'</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="kd">let</span> <span class="nx">api</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">authorize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'{access_token}'</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="nx">api</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">group</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">addTopic</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">id</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="nx">topic</span><span class="p">);</span>
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p>The above command returns JSON structured like this:</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight json tab-json"><code></code></pre>
<p>This endpoint adds a topic to a specific group. Only for admins.</p>
